<?xml version='1.0'  encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TeamHPPools_config>

<ShowHealthBar>true</ShowHealthBar> <!-- Display with healthbars or just text, true or false -->

<alliestext>$clanLogo &lt;img src='img://gui/maps/icons/formation/clan.png' width='28' height='28' align='baseline' vspace='-11'&gt; Allies ($teamHP)</alliestext> <!-- Text describing allied team hp pool. -->

<enemiestext>($enemyHP) Enemies &lt;img src='img://gui/maps/icons/formation/squad.png' width='28' height='28' align='baseline' vspace='-11'&gt; $clanLogo &lt;br/&gt;&lt;font size='10'&gt;&lt;i&gt;          HighCaliber ($HCvalue)&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/font&gt;</enemiestext> <!-- Text describing opposed team hp pool. -->

<healthbar>|</healthbar> <!-- Symbol the healthbar is made up of. Default is | -->

<AlliedBarColor>80FF00</AlliedBarColor> <!-- Color of the allied healthbar in HEX. Default is 80FF00 -->

<EnemyBarColor>EF0101</EnemyBarColor> <!-- Color of the allied healthbar in HEX. Default is EF0101 -->

</TeamHPPools_config>

<!--

Textmacros: 

$teamHP and $enemyHP for the respective total team HP pool sums.
$HCvalue for the total required damage in order to achieve the High Caliber medal.
$clanLogo to display the Clanlogo of the respective Team in CW or eSports matches.



The text also allows for HTML code if properly escaped html tags are used not to mess up XML parsing.

For example a linebreak tag would look like: &lt;br/&gt;

Bold text looks like this: &lt;b&gt; This text is BOLD. &lt;/b&gt;

font color tags: &lt;font color="#FF0000"&gt; This text is RED! &lt;/font&gt;

You can uses WoT built in images or your own as well, provided you know the path. For example the clan.png image inside gui.pkg is accessible by:

&lt;img src='img://gui/maps/icons/formation/clan.png' width='28' height='28' align='baseline' vspace='-11'&gt;

and so on and so forth...Enjoy.

To find out which HTML tags are supported by flash read this:
http://help.adobe.com/en_US/AS2LCR/Flash_10.0/help.html?content=00000307.html

-->